IRS990.Desc: THE RJCEF OPERATES DONOR-ADVISED FUNDS AS THE MAJOR PART OF ITS CHARITABLE OPERATIONS AND CONDUCTS ITS FUNDS IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE REQUIREMENTS IMPOSED FOR THE MAINTENANCE OF SUCH FUNDS.AT THE BEGINNING OF APRIL 2017, THE RJCEF MAINTAINED 2,783 DONOR ADVISED ACCOUNTS. DURING THE FISCAL YEAR AN ADDITIONAL 952 DONOR ADVISED FUNDS WERE ESTABLISHED WHILE 70 WERE CLOSED. THE NUMBER OF DONOR ADVISED ACCOUNTS AT THE END OF THE PERIOD WAS 3,665.DURING THE FISCAL YEAR, THE RJCEF MADE 17,023 CASH GRANTS TO DIFFERENT 501(C)(3) PUBLIC CHARITIES TOTALING $83,959,853. IN ADDITION, 175 GRANTS TOTALING $567,493 WERE ACCRUED DURING THE PERIOD BUT UNPAID AT FISCAL YEAR END. TOTAL GRANT EXPENSE AMOUNTED TO $84,527,346 OR 19.8% OF THE BEGINNING OF THE YEAR NET ASSETS WERE PAID OR ACCRUED. THE GRANTS WERE MADE TO ORGANIZATIONS IN THE FOLLOWING BROAD CATEGORIES:- 31.3% TO FAITH BASED AND RELIGIOUS ORGANIZATIONS- 18.3% TO SOCIAL SERVICE ORGANIZATIONS- 24.4% TO SCHOOLS AND EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTIONS- 7.0% TO MEDICAL AND SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH AND TREATMENT OF DISEASE- 4.4% TO THE ARTS AND MUSEUMS- 3.5% TO ENVIRONMENTAL AND ANIMAL ORGANIZATIONS- 11.1% TO VARIOUS OTHER PUBLIC CHARITABLE ORGANIZATIONS

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE ESTABLISHED BY DONORS TO SUPPORT GRANT EXPENSES, IN PERPETUITY.

THE RJCEF HAS EVALUATED THE EFFECT OF THE GUIDANCE ON ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES. MANAGEMENT BELIEVES THAT THE RJCEF CONTINUES TO SATISFY THE REQUIREMENTS OF A TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATION. MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED ALL OTHER TAX POSITIONS THAT COULD HAVE A SIGNIFICANT EFFECT ON THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND DETERMINED THE RJCEF HAD NO UNCERTAIN INCOME TAX POSITIONS AT MARCH 31, 2018.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE RJCEF DETERMINES GRANT QUALIFICATION AS FOLLOWS: 1) DONORS ARE PERMITTED TO SUBMIT A NON-BINDING, WRITTEN GRANT REQUEST TO THE RJCEF BOARD. THE RJCEF BOARD HAS DELEGATED TO RAYMOND JAMES TRUST, NA THE AUTHORITY TO MAKE GRANTS THAT MEET THE FOLLOWING CRITERIA: --THE MINIMUM GRANT IS $250 --THE ORGANIZATION RECEIVING THE GRANT MUST BE A U.S. PUBLIC CHARITY OR GOVERNMENTAL UNIT --THE GRANT MUST BE EXCLUSIVELY IN FURTHERANCE OF THE CHARITABLE ENTITY'S EXEMPT PURPOSE --THE GRANT MAY NOT CONFER A PRIVATE BENEFIT ON THE RJCEF DONOR 2) THE RJCEF CONFIRMS THAT THE ORGANIZATION TO RECEIVE THE GRANT IS, IN FACT, ELIGIBLE BY TAKING ONE OR MORE OF THE FOLLOWING STEPS, DEPENDING ON CIRCUMSTANCES, 1) REVIEWING IRS EXEMPT ORGANIZATION SELECT CHECK, 2) REQUESTING A COPY OF THE ORGANIZATION'S IRS DETERMINATION LETTER OR AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, 3) REQUESTING A COPY (OR REVIEWING VIA AN INTERNET WEB SITE) THE ORGANIZATION'S FORM 990. 3) THE RJCEF NOTIFIES THE GRANT RECIPIENT THAT ACCEPTANCE OF THE GRANT IS CONDITIONED UPON AN AGREEMENT NOT TO USE THE GRANT TO PROVIDE AN IMPERMISSIBLE BENEFIT TO THE RJCEF DONOR, DONOR ADVISER OR OTHER THIRD PARTY. 4) DEPENDING ON CIRCUMSTANCES THE BOARD MAY TAKE SUCH OTHER STEPS, AS IT DEEMS NECESSARY PRIOR TO APPROVING A GRANT. 5) THE RJCEF DOES NOT MAKE GRANTS TO PRIVATE NON-OPERATING FOUNDATIONS OR INDIVIDUALS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE RJCEF WILL NOT ENTER ANY BUSINESS TRANSACTION WITH ANY DIRECTOR OF THE FUND OR ANY ENTITY OF WHICH A DIRECTOR IS AN OFFICER, DIRECTOR, TRUSTEE, PARTNER, SOLE PROPRIETOR OR SHAREHOLDER (EXCEPT FOR ENTITIES OF WHICH THE DIRECTOR IS A SHAREHOLDER, THE SHARES OF WHICH ARE PUBLICLY TRADED AND THE DIRECTOR OWNS 5% OR LESS OF THE OUTSTANDING SHARES) IN WHICH IT MAKES A PAYMENT TO SUCH DIRECTOR OR SUCH ENTITY AND WILL NOT MAKE ANY CHARITABLE GRANT TO ANY DIRECTOR OR SUCH ENTITY UNLESS A MAJORITY OF THE OTHER DIRECTORS VOTE TO APPROVE SUCH TRANSACTION OR GRANT. BEFORE A DIRECTOR TAKES OFFICE AS SUCH OR, IN THE CASE OF A DIRECTOR SERVING ON THE DATE OF THE VOTE, WITHIN FIFTEEN DAYS AFTER SUCH DATE, AND, IN EITHER CASE, ON OR BEFORE EACH DECEMBER 31 THEREAFTER, HE OR SHE SHALL PROVIDE THE OTHER DIRECTORS WITH A WRITTEN LIST OF ALL SUCH ENTITIES. IN THE EVENT OF A POTENTIAL CONFLICT DURING THE YEAR, THE DIRECTOR WILL RECUSE HIMSELF/HERSELF FROM THE VOTE.
